[[Image:Stlouis-waters.jpg|thumb|Aloe Plaza across Market from Union Station]]
'''Aloe Plaza''' is part of the Terminus section of the [[St. Louis Gateway Mall]].  It is two blocks in size and sits directly in front of [[St. Louis Union Station|Union Station]].  It is bounded by [[Market Street (St. Louis)|Market]], [[Chestnut Street (St. Louis)|Chestnut]], [[18th Street (St. Louis)|18th]], and [[20th Street (St. Louis)|20th]] streets.

The plaza is dominated by the [[Carl Milles]] fountain ''The Meeting of the Waters''.

